Day 5 – Mock Interview

I'll ask you questions exactly like an interviewer:

Examples:

Explain abstraction with code.
Difference between interface and abstract class.
Explain Factory Pattern.
Design a Library Management System.
What is Velocity?
What is Story Point?
Explain Bridge Pattern with code.
Why use Proxy Pattern?
Difference between Composition and Inheritance.
Draw a Class Diagram for a Bank.
What are the SDLC phases?
Why Agile over Waterfall?
Explain Singleton with implementation.
Explain Observer Pattern with code.
What NOT to Study

Don't spend time on patterns your interviewer is unlikely to ask.

For example, skip these unless you have extra time:

Visitor
Interpreter
Flyweight
Memento
Chain of Responsibility
Template Method
Builder
Prototype
Composite
Decorator (unless you finish early)

Focus on the patterns your seniors specifically mentioned.

My Suggestion

Since we've already spent a lot of time together on:

JavaScript
OOP
Classes
Encapsulation
Inheritance
Polymorphism
Functional Programming

you're not starting from zero.

The biggest gaps are:

OOAD
