Those are exactly what we should focus on.

Here's how I'd like to help you over the next 5 days

Instead of giving you long theory, I'll teach each topic in an interview-first format:

🎯 2-minute concept
🎯 Real-world analogy
🎯 JavaScript implementation
🎯 UML (if applicable)
🎯 Common interview questions
🎯 Follow-up questions interviewers ask
🎯 A quick coding exercise (where relevant)

That approach will prepare you much more efficiently than reading notes alone, and it matches the style of questions your seniors were asked.




